[SN]TITLE[SN]
Why is immigration such a big issue in an election?

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The countdown to the general election is on. Tomorrow, adults across the country decide who they want to run the country.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
6 May 2015 Last updated at 06:42 BST
One of the big issues being talked about by politicians and the public is immigration.
Immigration is when people come into a country where they weren't born to live and work.
It's been happening for many years in the UK - but why do voters care about it so much?
Watch Ayshah's report to find out more.
